critical_positive: She was full of energy and seemed to really like small talk, so she kept the conversation going even though I was tired. We had plenty to talk about due to recent current events, and she had her move and things with her husband to share. She was pro-social and seemed to enjoy chatting with people in general.
critical_negative: Not knowing each other or having a similar lifestyle, we did not have things in common to get excited about, or at least not that were immediately apparent. I'm more of an independent, single, city girl, and she was more of a family lady into country life. She seemed like she was interested in what came on the TV, and I see TV as outdated technology that gives you only a narrow point of view.
